In the last few months, tomatoes had become a scarce commodity in the Kenyan markets, a move that saw prices shoot through the roof making almost impossible for small households to afford it. But for farmers like rev. Joseph Oloimooja from Maili Tisa in Namanga Kajiado County, this has been a money minting season and what sets him aside from other farmers, he does all this via his phone all the way from Los Angeles in the United States of America.